{
  "explanation": "The defendant's actions constitute a significant breach of professional trust given their role as an accountant. While the lack of a prior criminal record and the proactive attempt to repay a portion of the stolen funds serve as mitigating factors, the intentional nature of the embezzlement of $25,000 to cover personal debts necessitates a period of incarceration. A sentence of 12 months reflects the seriousness of the fiduciary breach while acknowledging the defendant's efforts toward restitution and low risk of recidivism.",
  "verdict": 12
}
